    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ducdauge.github.io/authors/emponti/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://ducdauge.github.io/authors/emponti/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I am a Lecturer (≈ Assistant Professor) in Natural Language Processing at the &lt;a href=&#34;https://edinburghnlp.inf.ed.ac.uk/&#34;&gt;University of Edinburgh&lt;/a&gt;, where I am part of the Institute for Language, Cognition, and Computation (&lt;a href=&#34;https://web.inf.ed.ac.uk/ilcc&#34;&gt;ILCC&lt;/a&gt;), and an Affiliated Lecturer at the &lt;a href=&#34;https://ltl.mmll.cam.ac.uk/&#34;&gt;University of Cambridge&lt;/a&gt;. I am a scientific advisor for the AI company &lt;a href=&#34;https://ivadolabs.com/en/&#34;&gt;Ivado Labs&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you are a prospective student, collaborator, or industry partner please visit the &lt;a href=&#34;faq&#34;&gt;FAQ&lt;/a&gt; page for more information.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previously, I was a visiting postdoctoral scholar at &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.stanford.edu/&#34;&gt;Stanford University&lt;/a&gt; and a postdoctoral fellow in computer science at &lt;a href=&#34;https://mila.quebec/en/&#34;&gt;Mila - Quebec AI Institute&lt;/a&gt; in Montreal. In 2020, I obtained a PhD in computational linguistics from the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.cam.ac.uk/&#34;&gt;University of Cambridge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.joh.cam.ac.uk/&#34;&gt;St John&amp;rsquo;s College&lt;/a&gt;. I interned as AI/ML researcher at &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.apple.com/&#34;&gt;Apple&lt;/a&gt; in Cupertino.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main research foci of my lab are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;sample efficiency&lt;/strong&gt;, learning from just a few examples by virtue of inductive biases and knowledge transfer;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;modular deep learning&lt;/strong&gt;, designing neural architectures that can better generalise to new tasks by recombining knowledge and updating it sparsely;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;grounding&lt;/strong&gt; language learning and use in perception and action;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;computational typology&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;multilingual NLP&lt;/strong&gt;, using computational tools to model the universals and variation of the world&amp;rsquo;s languages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My research earned a &lt;a href=&#34;https://ai.google/research/outreach/faculty-research-awards/&#34;&gt;Google Research Faculty Award&lt;/a&gt; and an &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.mmll.cam.ac.uk/news/prof-anna-korhonens-project-enabling-multilingual-conversational-ai-awarded-erc-proof-concept&#34;&gt;ERC Proof of Concept grant&lt;/a&gt; on multilingual conversational AI. I received 2 Best Paper Awards at &lt;a href=&#34;https://2021.emnlp.org/blog/2021-10-29-best-paper-awards/&#34;&gt;EMNLP 2021&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.aclweb.org/anthology/W19-4310.pdf&#34;&gt;RepL4NLP 2019&lt;/a&gt;. I am a board member of &lt;a href=&#34;https://sigtyp.github.io/&#34;&gt;SIGTYP&lt;/a&gt;, the ACL special interest group for computational typology, and a scholar of the European Lab for Learning and Intelligent Systems (&lt;a href=&#34;https://ellis.eu/fellows&#34;&gt;ELLIS&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
